{{Class 1|header=Threat Index: Class|hexagon=<span style="font-family:Overpass;">1</span>|color-h=50|color-s=50%|color-l=70%}}

'''Level 238''' is the 239<sup>th</sup> level of The Backrooms.

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|caption=The most infamous photograph of '''Level 238'''.|file=1777.webp}}
{{Blurimage|caption=A photograph of a hallway in '''Level 238'''.|file=Alsoalongload.jpg}}
{{Blurimage|caption=An image of a regular hotel room in '''Level 238'''.|file=338room.jpeg}}
'''Level 238''' resembles an extensive hotel's interior, conjoining at a particular courtyard in the perceived nucleus of the level. '''Level 238''' takes on modern and semi-luxurious architectural designs. Concrete comprises most of the level's structure, with walls adorned with decorative wallpaper having a drywall-like texture. Numerous locked doors populate '''Level 238''', sporting key card locks. When unlocked with certain key cards found throughout the level, opening a door leads one to a hotel room, rarely other levels or [[The Void]]. '''Level 238'''<nowiki/>'s temperature averages 12.5°C (54.5°F). The level has several vents providing airflow throughout the atrium and hallways across the edifice, regulating a cool climate.

The central atrium of '''Level 238''' extends 45 stories from top to bottom. The atrium's profile features jagged edges, whose silhouette is chaotic. The space has a featureless white concrete roof at the top, while at the bottom is a large park-like area, complete with fake greenery, theatrical props, pathways, benches, and garbage bins. A series of staircases across the atrium connect each floor, providing straightforward and reliable access to them. The courtyard is the loudest and coldest section of '''Level 238'''.

Several hallways protrude from the central courtyard into the far reaches of '''Level 238''', leading one into an interconnected network of hotel hallways extending roughly 550 km (340 mi) into the level's expanses. These hallways take on straight lines, although one may rarely encounter curved, zigzag hallways or abrupt sharp turns. Mini-lobbies are common, featuring elevators, a small lounging area, and a wall-mounted television displaying shows and media from [[the Frontrooms]]. The elevators are easy to access and do not require a special keycard. They lead to other floors of '''Level 238''' or, rarely, different levels. One may seldom find an Almond Water vending machine while traversing the hallways, requiring a keycard to dispense its contents.

Behind some doors are hotel rooms; these hotel rooms range in size, appearance, habitability, and utility. Most hotel rooms feature a king-size bed, rudimentary lighting, a television, a self-restocking mini-fridge containing various foodstuffs, and a bathroom with a shower, sink, and toilet. All the hotel rooms sport windows displaying either a dark, star-filled night sky, a nighttime view of a concrete building, or simply a black space resembling [[The Void]]. Most bathrooms, particularly those of lower-end hotel rooms, have a viciously impure water supply, in which the water resembles a dingy, dark brown sludge. Wanderers describe this water as having "a foul odor and a metallic taste." This water phenomenon only applies to water rushing from taps and showerheads.

The same doors sometimes lead to maintenance rooms instead of hotel rooms. These maintenance rooms have a hotter temperature than the rest of '''Level 238''' and contain various paraphernalia from equipment shelves, housekeeping carts, luggage trolleys, cleaning products, trash bags, maintenance equipment, electrical panels, and cool white fluorescent lights emitting a noise similar to that of [[Level 0]]. These rooms house freight elevators, allowing access to maintenance rooms on other floors. Laptops are commonplace in these rooms, which one can utilize to alter the broadcasts of '''Level 238'''<nowiki/>'s televisions. Rarely, one might encounter a dark green box in the maintenance rooms containing weapons and their respective ammunition. These weapons include pistols, submachine guns, and grenades.

Despite the level mainly taking on a modern appearance and architecture, venturing into '''Level 238'''<nowiki/>'s far expanses reveals hallways and rooms designed around the early 20th-century Art Deco style, [[Level 5]], and rococo designs. Minor ruins in the form of ceiling leaks, peeling paint, frayed wood and cloth, and dysfunctional lighting adorn the far expanses. Most doors within these regions are unopenable and unbudgeable. Doors unlock with regular keys rather than keycards, and more doors lead to [[The Void]] and other levels instead of regular hotel rooms. Elevators within these regions are inaccessible, and all televisions display static. These far-flung areas also contain a foul yet non-toxic mist inhibiting a mothball-like odor, provoking a gag reflex in many wanderers. The mist carrying the foul stench is slightly visible and usually hangs below waist height.
==Sentient Presence==
Hostile entities, including [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], [[Entity 36|Lighters]], [[Entity 5|Clumps]], [[Entity 8|Hounds]], and [[Entity 24|Refuse]]. Hostile entities only inhabit the decrepit, far-flung regions of '''Level 238'''.
==Colonies and Outposts ==
===New Greenwich ===
Founded on May 20, 2014, '''New Greenwich''' is a [[M.E.G.|Major Explorer Group]] settlement on '''Level 238'''. The name comes from Greenwich, a borough of London, a prominent [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] city, chosen due to the group's capital's name, New London. The base spans sixteen hotel rooms and has a stable population of 45. '''New Greenwich''' boasts a stable food and water supply. Their goals are to stockpile munitions found in maintenance rooms and to research more about '''Level 238'''. They are open to trading with other wanderers and will house wanderers for a short period if available. They are the level's largest and oldest group.
==Entrances and Exits==
{{Blurimage|caption=An image of a space in '''Level 238''' that transitions to [[Level 330]].|file=Notthegreatestbutok.png|width=370px}}
===Entrances===
*Entering a set of glass doors on [[Level 98]] sends one to the level's atrium;
*Any noclipping within a khrushchevka in [[Level 245]] sends one to the upper atrium floors;
*Noclipping through a wooden door on [[Level 330]] sends one to the level's atrium;
*Any noclipping during the Lights Out event in [[Level 184]] sends one here;
*Watching the show and episode "Creeped Out: The Many Place" until its conclusion in [[Level 40]] sends one here via noclipping.
===Exits===
*Noclipping through a patch of sakura-themed carpet sends one to [[Level 239]];
*Noclipping through a pile of concrete blocks sends one to [[Level 41]];
*Elevators heading above the top floor send one to [[Absolute Infinity Of Unknown]];
*A small open space featuring pools can transition to [[Level 330]];
*Entering a door with "PARKING" printed on it will lead to [[Level 917]];
*Noclipping through a room with severe water damage sends one to [[Level 427]];
*Rarely, some doors may lead to other [[Special:RandomInCategory/Levels|random Backrooms levels]], or [[The Void]].
